an style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">depend for their livelihoods</span><a name="_ftnref1"></a><a href="#_ftn1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">  </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> Within the sector, energy companies differ greatly from minerals companies</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> in terms of the technology they use, the number</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> of people they employ</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> and their physical footprint.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">BHP Billiton is the world’s leading diversified resources company.  </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">We </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">are one of the world's 25 largest publicly-listed companies</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> and one of the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">few</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> companies that </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">are</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">active in both mining and oil and</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> gas</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">.  </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">We </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">supply commodities globally and </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">have a presence in 26 countries </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">but </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">our largest operations </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">are in Australia, Chile and</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> the United States.  </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">We have a dual listed company structure, with primary listings on the Australian Stock Exchange (Limited)</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> and the London Stock Exchange (PLC). </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">We are one of the largest companies in the FTSE 100.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Our principal headquarters is in Australia but we also have </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">a significant corporate presence in the UK.  </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">The commodities we produce include the ingredients of </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">steel (iron ore, metallurgical coal and manganese) which is primarily used in construction and heavy equipment. We also produce copper</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">, which is </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">used in wiring</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> metals like aluminium and nickel which are used in industrial equipment and consumer goods</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> and</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> energy products like oil, gas, coal and uranium.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Our strategy is to own and operate a diverse portfolio of assets, covering multiple commodities, geographies, and markets. Our operations</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">are often in remote locations and are typically very large.  For ex</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">ample, at our Escondida copper mine in Chile’s Atacama Desert we move </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">approximately 1.3 million tonnes</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> of earth a day, the equivalent of excavating the Panama Canal twice a year. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">While we do not own or operate any mines in the UK, we </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">have interests in </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">a </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">development of five producing oil and gas fields in the Irish Sea and an oil and gas platform in the North Sea, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">most of </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">which are managed by our UK production unit in North Wales</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Our UK oil and gas business is</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> currently for sale.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Global c</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">ommodities</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> demand</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Economic growth</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> has helped to improve</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> living standards</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> g</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">lobally</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">I</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">ndustrialisation and urbanisation has lifted almost one billion people out of poverty in the last 20 years, with more </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">than 650 million of those people in China alone.  </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">The building </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">of cities and the development of industry requires </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">a secure supply of commodities</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> first </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">the steel making materials</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">used to build </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">housing</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">, infrastructure and an industrial base a</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">s well as </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">copper which is used in electricity grids.  A</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">s countries become wealthier, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">the use of </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">metals (like aluminium) </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">use</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">d</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> by a consumer economy</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> also grows while t</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">he demand for energy and food increases continually with development.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="8" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Demand for </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">commodities</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> which are crucial to the functioning </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">of </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">the global </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">economy will increase as the world’s population grows to 9 billion and incomes rise in the developing world.  </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">W</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">e predict the demand for commodities </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">will</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">grow </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">up to</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> 75 per cent</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">o</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">ver the next 15</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">years</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> alone</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">  </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="9" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Even with recycling and greater efficiency, we </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">will need to increase the production of basic commodities to meet the needs of a larger, wealthier </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">global </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">population</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">.  A well-functioning resources industry </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">will play an important part in continued </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">development</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">The many sources of supply</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="10" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Many countries</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> h</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">ave the potential to meet the</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> growing demand</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> for metals and energy</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">.  </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">The</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Earth’s crust</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> contains an abundance of </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">minerals</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">with hundreds of years of additional </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">potential </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">supply already identified</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">, which</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">means that geology is not the only factor when the industry considers where to invest.  A stable regulatory system, predictable taxation, a skilled work force and a political system that </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">facilitates broad-based economic benefit across the population</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> are al</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">l important </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">considerations</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="11" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">BHP Billiton’s </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">largest </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">operations </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">are in stable OECD countries</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> like Australia and Chile</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">We prefer countries in which </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">policy makers want to work with us, creating conditions for industry and </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">society more broadly </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">to prosper</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="12" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">We would like robust and efficient regulatory systems; foreign, fiscal and trade policies that encourage stability and open markets; and a modern industrial relations framework that enables dialogue between employers and employees. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="13" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">As the UK considers th</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">e future of its domestic natural resources industry, it will need to conduct a realistic assessment of its geology and approach the taxation and regulation of the sector </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">in a coordinated manner</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">.  </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">A </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">stable long term </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">framework </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">which sets</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> h</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">igh standards in re</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">gulation, environmental </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">management</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> and corporate governance</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">should </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">attract rather than deter </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">responsible </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">companies</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">  </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Economic benefits to the UK</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="14" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">The </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">UK</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> economy benefits both from the production of oil, gas and minerals at home and the global businesses of the resources industry.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> D</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">omestic oil and gas production has made a significant contribution to the economy </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">through job creation and </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">tax revenue</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> and th</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">e UK was a net exporter of petroleum until 2006.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="15" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">I</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">nternational resources companies </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">with a UK presence </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">pay tax, offer jobs </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">domestically and </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">world-wide to British nationals, are major customers of British engineering and advisory firms </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">and support research </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">at British universities. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 25.1pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="16" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Excluding contractors, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">BHP Billiton </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">employ</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> approximately 720 British nationals </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">world-wide </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">including our chief executive Andrew Mackenzie.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">  </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">We employ</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> 200 </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">people </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">in the UK, including employees at </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">our oil and gas operations </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">as wel</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">l as</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">investor relations, treasury, communications, finance, legal, company secretariat and marketing </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">teams</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">W</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">e also </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">employ </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">approximately 500 contractors</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> in our oil business and at our corporate centre in London.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 25.1pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="17" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Over the last five years BHP Billiton </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">has </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">pent over US$9 billion on British goods and services</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">, providing export opportunities for specialist firms</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">For example, o</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">ur Canadian potash project </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">has awarded </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">a £2.5m (US$3.9m) contract </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">to the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Kent-based Osprey Corporation for dryer wet scrubbers</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> and uses</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">British design services from South Yorkshire based Alan Auld. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="18" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Although most of BHP Billiton’s taxes are paid in the countries in which its largest businesses are based, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">we </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">made a substantial contribution of £84m (US$135m) </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">to the Exchequer </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">last year</span><a name="_ftnref2"></a><a href="#_ftn2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">.  </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Our global </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">effective </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">tax rate was 39.3 per cent in the most recent financial year. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="19" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">BHP Billiton</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> creates partnership</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> with British universities for the calibre of their research and their graduates</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">:</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Several British </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">universities</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">, including Nottingham, Car</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">diff, Southampton, Camborne School of Mines, and Imperial College</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> contribute to continuing multi-client research sponsored by the world’s leading mining companies. The projects are funded collaboratively by the mining industry through independent associat</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">ions, such as the Australian Minerals Industry Research Association (AMIRA), which ensures that the benefits are shared and that </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">the</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> institutions can retain their intellectual freedom.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">BHP Billiton is the lead sponsor of University College London’s Instit</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">ute for Sustainable Resources which generates research on the globally sustainable use of natural resources. We also contribute funds to UCL’s Australia campus where we support the Energy Policy Institute to provide an objective view of international devel</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">opments that have an impact on the energy sector and its participants.  We also have a research relationship with Bristol University, investing </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">US$</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">2.7</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> million over three years. </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">In the last</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> 20 years, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">over</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> ten per cent of geoscientists employed by BHP Bill</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">iton came from </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">British universities</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">. To improve the number of graduates from British universities entering BHP Billiton’s entry schemes, we have stepped up our </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">engagement at university career days and have reviewed our employment policies to make it easier</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> for British nationals to work at the company.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 25.25pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="20" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">The UK is a major financial centre for the mining and oil and gas industries</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> which pay more </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">than </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">28</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">% of dividends</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> in the FTSE 100 index of the UK’s largest firms</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">In a recent stud</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">y UK Trade &amp;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> Investment (UKTI) </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">reported that UK-listed mining companies had a total market capitalisation of £265bn (US$425bn) in 2012, more than any other financial market in the world.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 25.1pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="21" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Through our London listing, BHP Billiton PLC is in the top 20 largest companies </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">in the FTSE 100 index</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">.  Approximately 80% of shareholders in our PLC listing are </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">registered </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">in the UK</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">and British investors </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">have benefited directly from our performance.  In </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">our </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">case £100 invested in the company a decade ago would now be </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">worth </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">£700</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> includi</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">ng</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> the benefit of dividends. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Corporate governance</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> and regulation</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="22" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">The resources industry provides an opportunity for British investors to benefit from the rapid growth of emerging economies.  However,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> as</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> the standards and performance of resource companies can vary greatly, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">robust corporate governance standards are required to ensure that London retains its reputation for listing quality. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 25.1pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="23" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">The UK rules are among the most stringent in the world and</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> provid</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">ing they are applied consistently</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">size of the extractive</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">s sector relative to the London </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">market </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">should not be viewed </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">as</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> a cause for concern</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">.  </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 25.1pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="24" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Relaxing standards to attract listings would be bad for investors and companies like BHP Billiton that compl</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">y with the rules.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 25.1pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="25" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">However, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">BHP Billiton is concerned</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> that proposals from UK government departments, agencies and Parliamentarians are duplicating legislation which is already in train in the EU and other jurisdictions. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> This risks increasing compliance co</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">sts without enhancing performance.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 25.1pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="26" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">T</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">he more that can be done to achieve global standards</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">reduce the disparity between different regulatory regimes the better. For example, as a result of our two primary listings and our secondary listing on the New Yo</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">rk Stock Exchange we must comply with three separate regulatory regimes and reporting requirements for auditor independence. The UK government could </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">increase engagement</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> with other jurisdictions, especially Australia and the European Commission on regulator</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">y matters to ensure global standards exist.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Transparency</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="27" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">According to Transparency International, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">three</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> of the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">five </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">most transparent companies in terms of reporting are </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">UK listed</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">natural resources </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">companies.</span><a name="_ftnref3"></a><a href="#_ftn3">[3]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Mining, oil and steel companies make up six </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">of the top ten.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 25.1pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="28" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">BHP Billiton is a </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">founding</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> member of the Extractive Industries Transparency Initiative (EITI) which was conceived with significant assistance from the British government and we are represented on the EITI board. As a result of our EITI mem</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">bership we have publicly reported our payments to governments on a country-level basis since 2003. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="29" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Our view is that the UK’s membership of the EITI should not greatly increase costs for UK businesses since some are already reporting members, while many o</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">thers will now be captured by the reporting requirements of the recently passed EU Accounting and Transparency Directive. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="30" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">The UK’s membership of EITI makes it easier for the UK to demand higher standards of transparency in countries where governance is weak. Increasing legislation will not result in improved transparency. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Corporate social responsibility</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="31" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">We agree with th</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">e view expressed by Kofi Annan in th</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">is year’s</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> Africa Progress report, that mining and oil and gas companies can “</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">make a healthy profit while </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">also adhering to the highest international standards of social and environmental protection.”  We support initiativ</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">es that create a level playing field for the companies that wish to do so.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 25.1pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="32" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">There is</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> broad consensus within th</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">is year’s</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> G8</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> presidency</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> that the natural resources sector can play a greater role in enhancing development.  Resources companies benefit from stro</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">ng political governance and broad based economic growth </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">as</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> it improves the investment climate </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">and </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">ensures local sources of employe</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">es</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> and suppliers. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 25.1pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="33" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">We believe the</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> resources industry can do more to </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">improve governance</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">, build </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">strong public sector institutio</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">ns and </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">support </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">the development of small businesses in emerging economies.  Following a number of discussions with government, including those held at the G8 pre-summit on 15</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:8pt; vertical-align:super">th</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> June, BHP Billiton intends </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">to </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">increase its </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">focus on the</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">se</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> areas and</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> is ready to work with the Department for International Development and others to develop initiatives.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="34" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Our industry can make a substantial contribution to </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">development</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">.  </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Together, the largest London listed resource firms – Anglo America</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">n</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">, BHP Billit</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">on, Rio</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> Tinto, Xstrata </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">and BP</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> spent</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> over US$1 billion</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">on community programs </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">last year</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">, according </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">to their published data</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">BHP Billiton is one of the largest </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">voluntary </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">funders of community program</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> in the sector, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">investing </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">US$1.5 billion the last five years</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; margin-left:0pt"><tr><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:462.1pt"><ol start="35" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Making a difference in Mozambique</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Our “Mozal” aluminium smelter in Mozambique is a good illustration of how investments </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">by the natural resources industry </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">can support broader economic development</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">I</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">n 1998 Mozambique was emerging from 17 years of civil war</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> and making the difficult transition to a market based economy.  The country was hampered by weak institutions, few people had the training to build or work at a plant like Mozal</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> and malaria was endemic.  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Development of the project was backed by </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Mozambique</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> government, the UK, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">EU and </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Wor</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">l</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">d Bank to help:</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Attract foreign investors into Mozambique following the civil war; </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Improve local infrastructure, including vital health and educational services; </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Provide employment and training for local </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">people.  </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">With a budget of $1.2 billion, the project was the largest ever foreign investment </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">and largely achieved its goals. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Mozambique is expected to become a middle income country </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">and has received substantial overseas investment in recent years. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Mozal</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> has made a significant contribution </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">to </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">this progress. The smelter has </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">contributed</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> 3-6% of the country’s GDP each year.  It employs 1200 people and 600 contractors directly and contributes to indirect job creation of approximately 6500 people.  Thousands o</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">f people have trained at Mozal </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">and </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">93% of its employees are from Mozambique. The government is a shareholder and receives a proportional share of dividends.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Last year, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Mozal</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> spent approximately $460 million with local businesses, including over 150 small </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">suppliers that were established with support from Mozlink – an enterprise development program implemented by BHP Billiton to help spread the benefits of development. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">The construction of Mozal also supported the construction of new power lines bringing pow</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">er from South Africa to Mozambique </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">providing reliable power to</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> the south of </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">the country supporting development more broadly.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">The company’s successful healthcare programs have reduced the incidence of malaria in the local community from over 85% to less than 6%; and cut the HIV infection rate from 19% to 5%.  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">In addition, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">The Mozal Community Development Trust (MCDT) was establi</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">shed by BHP Billiton in 2000 </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">and</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> has initiated roughly 200 projects, focusing on quality of life, increasing access to healthcare, clean water and sanitation and poverty alleviation.</span></p></td></tr></table><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Working with NGOs</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="36" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">NGOs play an important role in helping BHP Billiton </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">develop its approach and responses to </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">social and environmental issues</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">.  Our Forum on Corporate Responsibility is a unique advisory body comprised of eight senior company executives, including the Group Chief Executive and the heads of each business unit, a</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">nd nine highly respected civil society leaders’ representatives from the regions in which we operate. The Forum has been a key component of our stakeholder engagement program since its inception in 1999, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">meeting </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">twice per year </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">on average </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">and contributing s</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">ignificantly to the development of our environment, community and security standards. Since 2009 we have instigated a four-year term for our civil society participants to </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">maintain</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> a fresh and diverse perspective.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="37" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">We also have long term partnerships with NGOs to help deliver major community investments. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">I</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">n South Africa and Mozambique, we work with PATH in our </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">$25 million </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">'Window of Opportunity' project to improve critical health and development services for 750,000 </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">pregnant women and young children up to two years of age. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> We also have a partnership with Conservation International</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> (CI)</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> to preserve biodiversity hotspots in the regions in which we operate.  Earlier this year, we announced a $20</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">.4</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> million </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">investment </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">to </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">preserve the Valdivian Coastal Reserve in Chile</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> with CI and the Nature Conservancy</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Conclusion</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 25.1pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="38" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">The UK has a number of strengths which </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">make it attractive to extractive companies</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">, including:</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Its </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">status as a major financial centre</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">The concentration of professional services firms, from </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">lawyers</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> to technical advisers, who support mining companies</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">The strong and stable legal and regulatory systems which provide clarit</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">y and confidence to investors</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Expertise</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> in the assessment of s</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">ocial an</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">d environmental impacts</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Globally respected think tanks that can influence the way natural resources companies approach development</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">And, u</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">niversities providing </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">world-leading research and high-quality</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> geoscience and en</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">gineering graduates</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="39" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">The </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">global scale </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">of the resource compan</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">ies</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> listed in the UK can also provide opportunities to support the government’s international</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> development</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> agenda</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> and</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span><a name="_GoBack"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">leveraging </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">the UK’s</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> role </span></a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">as a centre of influence</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="40" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">To ensure the country continues to benefit from the presence of </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">resources companies, we encourage the</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> robust implementation of the UK’s already high standards as well as greater dialogue between the UK and other jurisdictions in which international companies operate.  </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="41" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">The UK’s geology means it is unlikely to become a</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> major global supplier of raw materials. However the presence of resource companies provides secondary benefits which will contribute to the UK’s economy for many years to come; as a consumer of raw materials, a centre of influence, a global supplier to th</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">e industry, a focus for cutting-edge research and talent, and as a source of capital. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div><hr style="width:33%; height:1px; text-align:left" /><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn1"></a><a href="#_ftnref1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> Trends in the Mining and Metals Industry, International Council on Mining and Metals (ICMM), 2012</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn2"></a><a href="#_ftnref2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> Excludes employee taxes</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn3"></a><a href="#_ftnref3">[3]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic"> Transparency in Corporate Reporting, Transparency International, 2012</span></p></body></html>